The 23rd instalment of the South African Music Awards (SAMA) will be held at the Sun City Superbowl on 26 May.The luxury resort in the North West province is the official home for SAMA 23, having hosted 14 of the 22 previous ceremonies since its launch in 1994.An elated Nhlanhla Sibisi, CEO of RiSA, who are organising the awards, commented: "It's such a delight to be returning to Sun City. The convenience it brings during a weekend of celebration makes it the ideal location for us. We invite local music lovers to join the industry as it makes its trip to Sun City later in the year for a party fit for our country and the continent's finest musicians."With a number of music lovers that the awards attract, Sun City is sure to be abuzz with entertainment and loads of activities in and around Sun City.The SAMAs was hosted at the Durban ICC last year while Sun City underwent a massive multimillion-rand revamp.Source: The Juice